  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNESCO Brasilia Office will carry out a breakfast discussion round with national policy makers to generate an increased awareness of possible and future risks, challenges and trends concerning the enabling environment of intercultural dialogue among national policy makers. The second main objective of this activity is to organize an inter-agency Seminar, within the UN &quot;Vidas Negras&quot; (Black Lives) campaign, organized with the municipality of Porto Alegre, on &quot;Successful Experiences to fight against racism at municipal level&quot;, in partnership with the National Front of Mayors (FNP) and Montevideo Regional Office.</narrative>
